  "viewed_type": "CMessageView",
  "view_decl": "pub enum CMessageView {\n    GetRequest { k: CKey },\n    SetRequest { k: CKey, v: Option<Seq<u8>> },\n    Reply { k: CKey, v: Option<Seq<u8>> },\n    Redirect { k: CKey, id: EndPoint },\n    Shard { kr: KeyRange<CKey>, recipient: EndPoint },\n    Delegate { range: KeyRange<CKey>, h: CKeyHashMap },\n}\n\nimpl View for CMessage {\n    type V = CMessageView;\n    closed spec fn view(&self) -> CMessageView {\n        match self {\n            CMessage::GetRequest { k } => CMessageView::GetRequest { k: *k },\n            CMessage::SetRequest { k, v } => CMessageView::SetRequest {\n                k: *k,\n                v: match v {\n                    Some(b) => Some(b@),\n                    None => None,\n                },\n            },\n            CMessage::Reply { k, v } => CMessageView::Reply {\n                k: *k,\n                v: match v {\n                    Some(b) => Some(b@),\n                    None => None,\n                },\n            },\n            CMessage::Redirect { k, id } => CMessageView::Redirect { k: *k, id: *id },\n            CMessage::Shard { kr, recipient } => CMessageView::Shard { kr: *kr, recipient: *recipient },\n            CMessage::Delegate { range, h } => CMessageView::Delegate { range: *range, h: *h },\n        }\n    }\n}",
  "depends_on_views_of": [],
  "rationale": "CMessage is a tagged union of six wire-protocol messages whose every variant payload is spec-meaningful, so the projection is a parallel CMessageView enum that keeps all variants and fields. The dependency types CKey, EndPoint, KeyRange<CKey> and CKeyHashMap are uncovered leaves, so we carry them structurally (no @) following the same convention used for KeyIterator in KeyRange \u2014 once their View impls are synthesised a future pass can refine these fields recursively. The Vec<u8> payload is byte-order-sensitive, so we project it to Seq<u8> via Vec's standard view; the surrounding Option is unwrapped with an explicit match because vstd's `View for Option<T>` is the identity (only `DeepView` recurses), so we descend manually to obtain Option<Seq<u8>>.",
  "raw_response": "```json\n{\n  \"viewed_type\": \"CMessageView\",\n  \"view_decl\": \"pub enum CMessageView {\\n    GetRequest { k: CKey },\\n    SetRequest { k: CKey, v: Option<Seq<u8>> },\\n    Reply { k: CKey, v: Option<Seq<u8>> },\\n    Redirect { k: CKey, id: EndPoint },\\n    Shard { kr: KeyRange<CKey>, recipient: EndPoint },\\n    Delegate { range: KeyRange<CKey>, h: CKeyHashMap },\\n}\\n\\nimpl View for CMessage {\\n    type V = CMessageView;\\n    closed spec fn view(&self) -> CMessageView {\\n        match self {\\n            CMessage::GetRequest { k } => CMessageView::GetRequest { k: *k },\\n            CMessage::SetRequest { k, v } => CMessageView::SetRequest {\\n                k: *k,\\n                v: match v {\\n                    Some(b) => Some(b@),\\n                    None => None,\\n                },\\n            },\\n            CMessage::Reply { k, v } => CMessageView::Reply {\\n                k: *k,\\n                v: match v {\\n                    Some(b) => Some(b@),\\n                    None => None,\\n                },\\n            },\\n            CMessage::Redirect { k, id } => CMessageView::Redirect { k: *k, id: *id },\\n            CMessage::Shard { kr, recipient } => CMessageView::Shard { kr: *kr, recipient: *recipient },\\n            CMessage::Delegate { range, h } => CMessageView::Delegate { range: *range, h: *h },\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\",\n  \"depends_on_views_of\": [],\n  \"rationale\": \"CMessage is a tagged union of six wire-protocol messages whose every variant payload is spec-meaningful, so the projection is a parallel CMessageView enum that keeps all variants and fields. The dependency types CKey, EndPoint, KeyRange<CKey> and CKeyHashMap are uncovered leaves, so we carry them structurally (no @) following the same convention used for KeyIterator in KeyRange \u2014 once their View impls are synthesised a future pass can refine these fields recursively. The Vec<u8> payload is byte-order-sensitive, so we project it to Seq<u8> via Vec's standard view; the surrounding Option is unwrapped with an explicit match because vstd's `View for Option<T>` is the identity (only `DeepView` recurses), so we descend manually to obtain Option<Seq<u8>>.\"\n}\n```\n",
